  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But when Jesus saw it,.... Observed that his disciples reproved those that brought their children to, him, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "he was much displeased; with his disciples, who took too much upon them; for they ought first, to have known their master's will; whether it was his pleasure to grant the favour desired for these children, and not to have forbid them of themselves: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and said unto them; the disciples, as the Persic version reads: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "suffer the little children to come unto me, and forbid them not, for of such is the kingdom of God; or \"of them who\" are, , \"as these\", as the Syriac version, renders the words; or, as the Arabic, who \"are like to these\"; and the Persic, who are \"like to these little children\"; in innocence and humility; See Gill on Matthew 19:14. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "suffer the little children to come unto me, and forbid them not, for of such is the kingdom of God; or \"of them who\" are, , \"as these\", as the Syriac version, renders the words; or, as the Arabic, who \"are like to these\"; and the Persic, who are \"like to these little children\"; in innocence and humility; See Gill on ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 19:14",
            "children": []
          },
          {
